### Elixir and Erlang/OTP versions

Erlang/OTP 27 [erts-15.2.1] [source] [64-bit] [smp:10:10] [ds:10:10:10] [async-threads:1] [jit]

Elixir 1.20.0-rc.2 (0df45fd) (compiled with Erlang/OTP 27)

### Operating system

macOS

### Current behavior

Compiler/type checker hangs indefinitely when a function has multiple clauses that:

- Pattern match on different key sets in maps
- Another function with multiple clauses is called
- Have enough clauses (~20+)

## Example

```elixir
defmodule ElixirPatternIssue do
  # === KEY SET 1: matches only on `status` key ===
  def process(%{status: :pending}, _opts), do: {:ok, "Pending"}
  def process(%{status: :completed}, _opts), do: {:ok, "Completed"}

  # === KEY SET 2: matches on `category` + `kind` keys, but ACCESSES `status` ===
  def process(%{category: :alpha, kind: :primary} = data, opts) do
    with {:ok, ctx} <- context(opts[:context]), do: format(:alpha, data.status, ctx)
  end

  def process(%{category: :alpha, kind: :secondary} = data, opts) do
    with {:ok, ctx} <- context(opts[:context]), do: format(:alpha, data.status, ctx)
